I'll be sure to handle that in the morning  so for now  here's another attempt coming from me. Runnerguy2489's Ocarina of Time Bingo run was really fun to see  and hats off to NicroVeda's Odyssey run. Unfortunately  we reach the last hour or so of Summer Games Done Quick 2018. But as the saying goes  "all good things must come to an end " even if it's only temporary. That being said  the $5 goes to Wrexsoul  even if it's closed. It's not much coming from me  but I'd say it's enough. By the way  if this donation goes through  it'll be my second donation ever to GDQ  wheras the last one was my first. So  here's a shoutout to everyone who made this run a Glitchless 100%  as well as making the incentives happen. I heard some amazing singing and loved every second of the Suplex against the Phantom Train. I'm also giving a shoutout to my high school's athletic director  who is currently trying to suplex cancer. I'll be supporting you all the way! With that in mind  there is one request I'd like to give to the chat  audience  and whoever else so we can end this run with the hypest of HYYYPE! Once the final battle with Kefka comes along  and it'll be time to land the final attacks on him  can we chant  "BEAT THAT CLOWN! BEAT THAT CLOWN!" if that's alright? With that in mind  good night  and good luck.

This SGDQ is the second  I'm able to watch and it's absolutely awesome. Thanks to all the runners  the GDQ-Crew  the people in the chat and all around the globe on their screens for making and supporting this remarkable charity event. Two days ago I got the message  I will lose my job til end of july. I was absolutely down and sad  but the SGDQ cheered me up again with their unique people  humour and positive attitude. So take this 50 Dollars from me  all of you deserve it. And now go for this 2 million dollars! By the way: is your couch still comfy after 6 hours FF6? Mine is ;-)

Ill drop an additonal 5$ if during the scene where Kefka turns all the espers into Magicate  one of the couch says "One  two  skip a few  ALL OF YOU!" in the most sinister  mad  Kefka voice they can do.

*AHEM* Minecart passage is NOT mode 7. Mode 7 can only scale a single contiguous background layer. Minecart has ALL KINDS of overlapping going on. As far as I can discern  minecart passage is actually a zillion sprites being juggled at once  with various scales of premade art being swapped on the fly. So yes  still pushing SNES to its limit (1 zillion is basically all 128 SNES sprites)  but NOT mode 7.

There once was this marathon called GDQIt started off small  with but a few"Speedrunners" they're called  they like to go fastBy blazing through games and having a blastAs the years went by it got bigger and biggerThe tricks they performed got sicker and sickerBut for fun this was not only performedAs the words "For Charity" blazed across the boardThey do this for fun  but raising money is the main goalFor charities in need they perform from their soulSo thank you from the runners to the donors and orgsFor not only keeping the many from being boredBut for collecting donations that rank in the millionsAnd the words "Charity Marathon" is respected by billionsSGDQ is on top of the packTaking the time to fill up the sackOf any charity that comes their wayBut it's Doctors Without Borders that shines today! Cheers and Love to all involved! You are all superstars!

There once was this marathon called GDQIt started off small  with but a few"Speedrunners" they're called  they like to go fastBy blazing through games and having a blastAs the years went by it got bigger and biggerThe tricks they performed got sicker and sickerBut for fun this was not only performedAs the words "For Charity" blazed across the boardThey do this for fun  but raising money is the main goalFor charities in need they perform from their soulSo thank you from the runners to the donors and orgsFor not only keeping the many from being boredBut for collecting donations that rank in the millionsAnd the words "Charity Marathon" is respected by billionsSGDQ is on top of the packTaking the time to fill up the sackOf any charity that comes their wayBut it's Doctors Without Borders that shines today! Cheers and Love!! There once was this marathon called GDQIt started off small  with but a few"Speedrunners" they're called  they like to go fastBy blazing through games and having a blastAs the years went by it got bigger and biggerThe tricks they performed got sicker and sickerBut for fun this was not only performedAs the words "For Charity" blazed across the boardThey do this for fun  but raising money is the main goalFor charities in need they perform from their soulSo thank you from the runners to the donors and orgsFor not only keeping the many from being boredBut for collecting donations that rank in the millionsAnd the words "Charity Marathon" is respected by billionsSGDQ is on top of the packTaking the time to fill up the sackOf any charity that comes their wayBut it's Doctors Without Borders that shines today!

There once was this marathon called GDQIt started off small  with but a few"Speedrunners" they're called  they like to go fastBy blazing through games and having a blastAs the years went by it got bigger and biggerThe tricks they performed got sicker and sickerBut for fun this was not only performedAs the words "For Charity" blazed across the boardThey do this for fun  but raising money is the main goalFor charities in need they perform from their soulSo thank you from the runners to the donors and orgsFor not only keeping the many from being boredBut for collecting donations that rank in the millionsAnd the words "Charity Marathon" is respected by billionsSGDQ is on top of the packTaking the time to fill up the sackOf any charity that comes their wayBut it's Doctors Without Borders that shines today! CHEERS AND LOVE!!

There once was this show called GDQThat started out with only a fewBut little did they know how big they'd growShow after show the runs got quickerThe tricks and skips got sicker and sickerAll the while raising much needed moneyWith a week of entertainment both enduring and funnyWe all come together to help one big causeAnd the last thing on the runner's mind is hitting pauseDoctors Without Borders helps all over the worldHelping anyone they can  so I've been toldSo open your wallets  and watch some runsWho knew this could be so much fun?But from humble beginnings to the beast it is nowAll you can do is sit back and say wowFor what they achieve year after yearIs absolutely nothing short of unrealAnd from the runner  to the donator we thank you allA week of love and respect  that we all callSGDQ - Summer Games Done QuickA great group of people  who help charities "hit a lick" Cheers and Love!

#MIBA I had to donate during a run of probably the most important game of my life. As a kid  I fell in love with Wind Waker in 1st grade when I got the game for Christmas. Playing the game made me decide that I wanted to go to school to make video games. That dream fueled me all throughout school until I was able to find Ferris State University and the Digital Animation and Game Design program there. By going to school there  I was able to meet my boyfriend  form a dance company  and meet my current group of friends  and one of those friends is why I’m sitting here in back couch at SGDQ right now. Basically  I have Wind Waker to thank for everything great that has happened in my life. Thank you so very much to Linkus7 for running such a wonderful game at such a wonderful event.

I've donated before.  I could try to wax poetic about how this game was one of my favorites  but the truth is... I never played it. I could try to describe how my life was truly changed by the great charity that is Doctor's Without Borders... but I've been lucky enough in my life to never need their help. So in the end I am left with $25 so uh... here... go do the thing! column1: It's getting late here but we had to stay up to watch what we know will be an exciting race.

column1: The FitnessGram™ Pacer Test is a multistage aerobic capacity test that progressively gets more difficult as it continues. The 20 meter pacer test will begin in 30 seconds. Line up at the start. The running speed starts slowly  but gets faster each minute after you hear this signal. [beep] A single lap should be completed each time you hear this sound. [ding] Remember to run in a straight line  and run as long as possible. The second time you fail to complete a lap before the sound  your test is over. The test will begin on the word start. On your mark  get ready  start.

column2: To be fair  you have to have a very high IQ to understand Games Done Quick . Hey its n3rds from the back couch.  I have the consistant setup for slingshot skip coming in hot. Steps:1. Lift your leg up behind you.2. Spin around for about 1 second.3. Stop.4. Double take 3 times.5. Pelvic thrust to your left  then back to your right.6. Stop on your right foot as you come back to your right after the pelvic thrust. (Don't forget it!)7. "Bring it around town" by spinning your torso in a circle around the air.8. Jump around for about 6 seconds.9. And that's how you skip the slingshot

Good evening SGDQ! Given the recent decision from the World Health Organization to create a "gaming disorder" classification  it seems more important than ever to donate to an organization that has done so much good for our amazing community. As an Assistant Professor who researches gaming and gaming behavior  please know that not all PhD's and clinicians are in support of the WHO's ruling. Our aim is to promote the great communities that exist in gaming and help others understand our passion that much more. Thank you so much for holding this event! Save the frames  save the animals.
